<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id525d24bb-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6" identifier="/us/usc/t28/s504a"><num value="504a">§ 504a.</num><heading> Associate Attorney General</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The President may appoint, by and with the advice and consent of the Senate, an Associate Attorney General.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id525d24bc-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/95/139/s1/a">Pub. L. 95–139, § 1(a)</ref>, <date date="1977-10-19">Oct. 19, 1977</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/91/1171">91 Stat. 1171</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
